what is ec2 instance?
An EC2 instance is a virtual server in the cloud provided by Amazon Web Services (AWS) that you can use to run applications. 
It functions like a physical computer, allowing you to choose the operating system, CPU, memory, and storage you need, and you only pay for what you use. 
This provides scalability (Elastic Compute Cloud) to adjust resources as needed. 

types of ec2 instance?
An AWS instance type is a choice of virtual machine that determines the CPU, memory, storage, and networking capacity available for your application. 
AWS provides a wide variety of instance types, which are grouped into categories like General Purpose, Compute Optimized, Memory Optimized, and Storage Optimized,
to help you match your specific workload needs to the right mix of resources. 

What an instance type determines
CPU: The processing power for your instance.
Memory: The amount of RAM available to your instance.
Storage: The type and amount of storage, such as EBS (Elastic Block Store) or local NVMe SSDs, is available to your instance.
Networking: The network and disk subsystem capacity, including network bandwidth, is allocated to your instance. 

what type of instance family you used in your project?
 we use R-Family , because our 3-tier application largely deals with database if you configure any type of R 
 R-series (Memory Optimized) – Best for most databases
Examples: R6g, R6i, R7g, R7i
Why?
Databases like MySQL/PostgreSQL/Oracle/MongoDB run best when most working data fits in memory.
High RAM → faster read queries.
Good balance of CPU + memory.
Use if:
You have high read/write load
Large DB cache
In-memory operations are important
✅ Most commonly used in real-time projects

