 what is AMI?
 “An AMI is a pre-configured template that contains the operating system, application software, and configuration required to launch an EC2 instance. 
 It acts as a blueprint for creating identical servers and is commonly used for scaling and automation.”

what is EBS?
“EBS (Elastic Block Store) is durable, block-level storage for EC2 instances. It acts as a virtual hard disk where we store the OS, logs, database files, and application data. 
EBS volumes are persistent, can be backed up using Snapshots, and come in multiple types like gp3 and io2 depending on IOPS and throughput requirements.”
